Usage: set_pll_timing [-help] <inst_name> -feedback_pin < fedback pin name>
                      -output_clock < clock name or ID>
                      -output_pin < output pin name>
                      [-reference_edge {rise fall both}]
                      -reference_pin < reference pin name>

-help                                 # Prints out the command usage
<inst_name>                           # instance on which we will search ref
                                      # pin, feedback pin , output_pin
                                      # (string, required)
-feedback_pin < fedback pin name>     # PLL feedback pin (string, required)
-output_clock < clock name or ID>     # PLL output clock (string, required)
-output_pin < output pin name>        # PLL output pin (string, required)
-reference_edge {rise fall both}      # Defines adjustment edge(s)
                                      # (enum, optional)
-reference_pin < reference pin name>  # PLL reference pin (string, required)